raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "8.1.5" %}

package:
  name: thinc
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/t/thinc/thinc-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 4d3e4de33d2d0eae7c1455c60c680e453b0204c29e3d2d548d7a9e7fe08ccfbd

build:
  number: 0
  script: {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . --no-deps -vv

requirements:
  build:
    - python                                 # [build_platform != target_platform]
    - cross-python_{{ target_platform }}     # [build_platform != target_platform]
    - cython                                 # [build_platform != target_platform]
    - numpy                                  # [build_platform != target_platform]
    - {{ compiler('cxx') }}
  host:
    - cython <3.0
    - python
    - pip
    - numpy
    - setuptools
    - wheel
    - cymem >=2.0.2,<2.1.0
    - preshed >=3.0.2,<3.1.0
    - murmurhash >=1.0.2,<1.1.0
    - cython-blis >=0.7.8,<0.8.0
  run:
    - python
    - {{ pin_compatible('numpy') }}
    - murmurhash >=1.0.2,<1.1.0
    - cymem >=2.0.2,<2.1.0
    - preshed >=3.0.2,<3.1.0
    - cython-blis >=0.7.8,<0.8.0
    - wasabi >=0.8.1,<1.1.0
    - srsly >=2.4.0,<3.0.0
    - catalogue >=2.0.4,<3.0.0
    - confection >=0.0.1,<1.0.0
    - pydantic >=1.7.4,!=1.8,!=1.8.1,<1.11.0
    - typing_extensions >=3.7.4.1,<4.2.0  # [py<=37]

test:
  requires:
    - hypothesis
    - pytest
    - mock
    - pathy >=0.3.5
  imports:
    - thinc
    - thinc.api
    - thinc.linear
    - thinc.extra
    - thinc.neural

  commands:
    - python -m pytest --tb=native --pyargs thinc

about:
  home: https://github.com/explosion/thinc/
  license: MIT
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: 'thinc: a lightweight deep learning library'
  description: |
    A refreshing functional take on deep learning, compatible with your
    favorite libraries

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - rmax
    - honnibal
    - ines
    - adrianeboyd
